  "text": "The offset commit path flows as follows: (1) KafkaConsumer.commitSync() is a thin facade that delegates to either ClassicKafkaConsumer or AsyncKafkaConsumer. (2) ClassicKafkaConsumer.commitSync() calls ConsumerCoordinator.commitOffsetsSync() which sends an OffsetCommitRequest to the broker. (3) On the broker, KafkaApis.handleOffsetCommitRequest() (Scala) receives the request and calls groupCoordinator.commitOffsets(). (4) GroupCoordinator is an interface; GroupCoordinatorService implements commitOffsets() and dispatches to the CoordinatorRuntime which calls GroupCoordinatorShard.commitOffset(). (5) The shard delegates to OffsetMetadataManager.commitOffset() which validates the request, builds CoordinatorRecord objects via GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.newOffsetCommitRecord(), and returns a CoordinatorResult. (6) The CoordinatorRuntime appends those records to the __consumer_offsets partition via PartitionWriter.append(), which is the final log write.",
